answers.body_markdown:
They are arguments of the method `__init__`. If you specify a value using `=` after the name of the argument, it will be the default value of this argument.

Some examples

```
&gt;&gt;&gt; m1 = Mother(&quot;Juliana&quot;, &quot;123 Apple Street&quot;)
&gt;&gt;&gt; m2 = Mother(&quot;Francisca&quot;)
&gt;&gt;&gt; m3 = Mother()
&gt;&gt;&gt; m1.strName
&#39;Jualiana&#39;
&gt;&gt;&gt; m1.strAddress
&#39;123 Apple Street&#39;
&gt;&gt;&gt; m2.strName
&#39;Francisca&#39;
&gt;&gt;&gt; m2.strAddress
&#39;717 Lynx Street&#39;
&gt;&gt;&gt; m3.strName
&#39;Maya&#39;
&gt;&gt;&gt; m3.strAddress
&#39;717 Lynx Street&#39;
```

You are applying class inheritance to your class `Son`. This means that it will inherit all the instance variables and methods from your base class `Mother`. Therefore, you are inheriting the `__init__` method which uses those default values.

